Wash and dry produce.

Trim and roughly chop @scallions{2}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Dice @tomato{1}. Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallions, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}. Stir in a pinch of garlic and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Taste and add more garlic and lime juice as needed.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add tomato and remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1/2 cup water, @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @organic chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with remaining @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, slice chicken crosswise.

> Swap in chicken or organic chicken for pork; cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side.

While chicken cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, half the lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and a big pinch of salt. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, remaining lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper.

Divide rice and chicken between plates. Top rice with bean mixture and crema. Top chicken with salsa. Cut any remaining lime into wedges and serve on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.